derivation.yuyuan_name: late 16th cent. (in the sense 'existing only in name'): from French titulaire or modern Latin titularis, from titulus (see title)

entry.tran: 名义上的;有名无实的;徒有虚名的
entry.def: A titular job or position has a name that makes it seem important, although the person who has it is not really important or powerful.
